For each specific value of iii, x[i]x[i]x[i] will take one of the follwing cases: if x[i]≥tx[i] \geq tx[i]≥t , iii increases and goes on traversing; else if x[i]tx[i] x[i]t , x[i]x[i]x[i] will be swapped to the left part, as statement swap(x[++m], x[i]) does. Partition is done when i == u, and then we apply quick sort to the left and right parts, recursively. Under what circumstance does recursion terminate? Yes, l >= u.
